		<div class="post" id="post-508">
		<h1 class="title">2011-12 Seminar Series</h1>
		<div class="entry">
			<p>The Center for Game Culture and Virtual Worlds is proud to kick off its 2011-12 Distinguished Speaker Series with a panel of speakers.</p>
<p>All lectures will be held in <a title="Campus Map" href="http://www.uci.edu/campusmap/index.php" target="_blank">6011 Donald Bren Hall</a> at the University of California, Irvine unless otherwise noted below.</p>
<p>The Series is open to the public at no charge. Video recordings of some of the seminars are available below.</p>
<table style="height: 77px;" width="723" border="1">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th width="104">Date</th>
<th width="286">Title</th>
<th width="311">Speakers</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left;">Wednesday, October 5, 2011</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">5:00-7:00 p.m.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">DBH 6011</p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>&#8220;</strong><a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~develop/Lectures/CGVWTalk100511_MP4%20360p%20(16x9).mp4">Understanding the games and the business of the games business</a><strong>&#8220;</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: left;">
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.inxile-entertainment.com/about">Brian Fargo</a>, CEO, inXile entertainment</li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.readyatdawn.com/ru.html">Ru Weerasuriya</a>, Founder, Ready at Dawn Studios</li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.mobygames.com/developer/sheet/view/developerId,64157/">Lee Jacobson</a>, Senior VP, Atari Inc.</li>
</ul>
